connect

public void connect(fb.xml.mgt.FBMConnection cnxn)
             throws FBRManagementException
Makes the connection specified by the given element. If the connection already exists, the command is ignored. If it is a data connection to an existing destination, the new source variable silently replaces the old one on the connection list.

Parameters:
cnxn - FBMConnection
Throws:
FBRManagementException - NO_SUCH_OBJECT if the source or destination FB does not exist, or INVALID_OBJECT if a requested endpoint does not exist.

queryFB

public fb.xml.FBElement queryFB(fb.xml.mgt.FBMFB fb)
                         throws fb.xml.XMLException,
                                FBRManagementException
If the name of the given FB is not "*" and the type is not "*", returns the argument if it exists in the managed FB list. If the name is not "*" and the type is "*", returns the managed FB with the given name if any. If the name is "*" and the type is not "*", returns a list of names of FBs of the given type. If the name and type are both "*", returns a list of names of all managed FBs.

Parameters:
fb - FBMFB
Returns:
FBElement
Throws:
fb.xml.XMLException - INVALID_OBJECT.
FBRManagementException - NO_SUCH_OBJECT.

read

public fb.xml.FBElement read(fb.xml.FBElement obj)
                      throws fb.xml.XMLException,
                             FBRManagementException
Reads the value of the variable specified by the source or destination field. The other field must be "*".

Parameters:
obj - Must be an FBConnection.
Returns:
A connection with the "*" field replaced by the value of the variable.
Throws:
fb.xml.XMLException - Will cause an INVALID_OBJECT response.
FBRManagementException - Will cause a NO_SUCH_OBJECT response.
